"content":"Admin; imports disabled."},"651":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-77","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"Running a workflow (`POST /api/workflows/{id}/run`, `run_workflow`) and preflighting it are covered on the Runs page."},"652":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","type":"page","content":"Building agents on Runyard","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Guides"],"tags":[],"url":"/guides/agent-consumers"},"653":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-0","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers","content":"Discovery surfaces, the API-first guarantee, and recommended etiquette for agents and third-party clients."},"654":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-1","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"Discovery surfaces"},"655":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-2","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/agent-consumers#the-api-first-guarantee","content":"The API-first guarantee"},"656":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-3","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/agent-consumers#auth-expectations","content":"Auth expectations"},"657":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-4","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/agent-consumers#recommended-agent-etiquette","content":"Recommended agent etiquette"},"658":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-5","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/agent-consumers#push-instead-of-poll-response-endpoints","content":"Push instead of poll: response endpoints"},"659":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-6","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/agent-consumers#machine-intake-workflow-endpoints","content":"Machine intake: workflow endpoints"},"660":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-7","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers","content":"Runyard treats agents as first-class API consumers. This page covers how a client discovers what a Hub can do, what it may rely on, and how to be a good citizen."},"661":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-8","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"Surface"},"662":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-9","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"Auth"},"663":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-10","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"What it gives you"},"664":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-11","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"`GET /llms.txt`"},"665":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-12","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"none"},"666":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-13","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"Static, generic orientation for agents: what Runyard is, its tool names, the run path. It deliberately contains nothing deployment-specific and points at the authenticated menu."},"667":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-14","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"`GET /openapi.json`"},"668":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-15","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"none"},"669":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-16","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"The full HTTP surface, generated from the Hub's API surface registry — it cannot drift from the routes the server actually registers."},"670":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-17","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"MCP `tools/list`"},"671":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-18","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"token"},"672":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-19","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"The complete MCP tool set (parity-tested against the API surface). Connect with `runyard mcp install` or the `runyard-mcp` stdio server."},"673":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-20","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"`GET /api/menu` / `get_menu`"},"674":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-21","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"token"},"675":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-22","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"The live, private catalog: workflows with schemas, execution modes, runner pool state, and ready-to-use CLI/MCP invocations."},"676":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-23","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"Start every session with `get_menu` (or `GET /api/menu`), then `describe_workflow` for anything you intend to run."},"677":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-24","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#the-api-first-guarantee","content":"The web app is an ordinary client of the same HTTP API, with no privileged endpoints. Every route is declared in one registry that also generates `openapi.json` and is parity-tested against the MCP tool list — so a lossless third-party client is possible by construction: anything the web app can show or do, your client can too, over HTTP or MCP."},"678":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-25","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#auth-expectations","content":"Ask the Hub's administrator for a scoped access token (admins issue them from the Connect tab or `POST /api/tokens`). Agents typically need `api` and/or `mcp` — nothing more. Send it as `Authorization: Bearer <token>` on every HTTP call, or configure it for the MCP server. Never ask for or expect the bootstrap/admin token."},"679":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-26","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#recommended-agent-etiquette","content":"**Set `input.title`.** For agent-created runs, include a short human-readable title (\"Audit checkout flow mobile states\") so run lists, approval cards, and human handoff stay decipherable."},"680":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-27","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#recommended-agent-etiquette","content":"**Preflight first.** When input is rough or unverified, call `preflight_workflow` (`POST /api/workflows/{id}/preflight`) or pass `negotiate: true` to `run_workflow`. You get `ready | needs_input | blocked` with concrete questions and blockers instead of a run that fails."},"681":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-28","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#recommended-agent-etiquette","content":"**Use run drafts for question/answer loops.** `create_run_draft` creates a proposed run and preflights it; `update_run_draft` merges answers into the input and re-preflights; `submit_run_draft` enqueues the real run only once it is ready; `discard_run_draft` abandons it. Nothing executes until submit."},"682":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-29","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#recommended-agent-etiquette","content":"**Poll the timeline with `since` cursors.** `get_run_timeline` (`GET /api/runs/{id}/timeline`) returns a unified, ascending view of status transitions, events, and artifacts. Pass the previous response's `nextSince` as `since` so the Hub never re-sends what you have. Fetch results with `get_run_status`, `get_run_logs`, and `get_run_artifacts` / `download_artifact`."},"683":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-30","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#push-instead-of-poll-response-endpoints","content":"`POST /api/workflows/{id}/run` accepts an optional `responseEndpoint` (`{ \"type\": \"http\" | \"telegram\", \"config\": { ... } }`). When the run reaches a terminal state, the Hub POSTs a sanitized payload to your HTTP endpoint (or sends a concise Telegram message). Delivery state is visible on `GET /api/runs/{id}` under `responseEndpoints[]`, and polling remains the canonical fallback."},"684":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-31","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#machine-intake-workflow-endpoints","content":"For fixed-purpose integrations that should not hold a Hub token at all (webhooks, form intake, external systems), an admin can configure a **workflow endpoint**: `POST /api/workflow-endpoints/{slug}` accepts a payload authenticated with that endpoint's own secret, rate-limited, size-capped, and deduplicated, and triggers exactly one preconfigured workflow. This is the narrowest possible credential to hand to an external system."},"685":{"id":"/guides/api","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"page","content":"HTTP API","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Guides"],"tags":[],"url":"/guides/api"},"686":{"id":"/guides/api-0","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api","content":"Authenticate, discover, and drive workflow runs over the Runyard Hub's HTTP API."},"687":{"id":"/guides/api-1","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"Authentication"},"688":{"id":"/guides/api-2","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/api#discovery","content":"Discovery"},"689":{"id":"/guides/api-3","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"API groups and `/api/v1` aliases"},"690":{"id":"/guides/api-4","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/api#the-typical-flow","content":"The typical flow"},"691":{"id":"/guides/api-5","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Key endpoints"},"692":{"id":"/guides/api-6","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/api#approvals","content":"Approvals"},"693":{"id":"/guides/api-7","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/api#run-drafts","content":"Run drafts"},"694":{"id":"/guides/api-8","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/api#error-conventions","content":"Error conventions"},"695":{"id":"/guides/api-9","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/api#rate-limits","content":"Rate limits"},"696":{"id":"/guides/api-10","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/api#see-also","content":"See also"},"697":{"id":"/guides/api-11","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api","content":"Every Runyard surface — the web app, the CLI, and the MCP server — is an\nordinary client of one HTTP API served by the Hub. Anything they can do, you\ncan do with `curl`."},"698":{"id":"/guides/api-12","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"Send an access token as a bearer token on every request:"},"699":{"id":"/guides/api-13","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"Tokens are minted by an admin (web UI, `POST /api/tokens`, or the CLI) and carry\n**scopes**:"},"700":{"id":"/guides/api-14","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"Scope"},"701":{"id":"/guides/api-15","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"Grants"},"702":{"id":"/guides/api-16","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"`api`"},"703":{"id":"/guides/api-17","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"Start runs, preflight, drafts, rerun/cancel/promote, create approvals"},"704":{"id":"/guides/api-18","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"`mcp`"},"705":{"id":"/guides/api-19","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"The same operations, issued for MCP clients"},"706":{"id":"/guides/api-20","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"`read`"},"707":{"id":"/guides/api-21","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"**Read-only** — inspect workflows, runs, logs, artifacts, approvals, schedules, and runners; satisfies no mutation endpoint"},"708":{"id":"/guides/api-22","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"`runner`"},"709":{"id":"/guides/api-23","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"The runner protocol: register, heartbeat, claim runs, report lifecycle events and artifacts"},"710":{"id":"/guides/api-24","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"`approvals`"},"711":{"id":"/guides/api-25","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"Resolve approval cards (approve / reject / request changes) and create them"},"712":{"id":"/guides/api-26","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"`admin`"},"713":{"id":"/guides/api-27","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"**Superscope** — satisfies every scope requirement, plus admin-only surfaces: tokens, secrets, audit log, schedules, workflow create/update, packages, hooks, updates"},"714":{"id":"/guides/api-28","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"`GET /api/tokens/scopes` (admin) returns this vocabulary plus named presets —\n**everything** (`api`+`mcp`+`approvals`, the default), **read-only**,\n**approvals-only**, **runner**, and **admin** — which the Tokens page uses."},"715":{"id":"/guides/api-29","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"Reads such as listing runs, workflows, or artifacts require any authenticated\ntoken. A token with only the `read` scope is therefore read-only: it can\ninspect everything non-admin but every create/update/delete/run/approve call\nfails with `403`. A request with no valid token gets\n`401 {\"error\": \"unauthorized\"}`; a token missing a required scope gets:"},"716":{"id":"/guides/api-30","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"with status `403`. `GET /api/me` describes the calling token (name and scopes)."},"717":{"id":"/guides/api-31","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#discovery","content":"**`GET /openapi.json`** (unauthenticated) — generated from the server's API\nsurface registry, the single source of truth every route is registered from,\nso **every endpoint is documented there**. This guide covers the important\nones; use `/openapi.json` for the full list."},"718":{"id":"/guides/api-32","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#discovery","content":"**`GET /api/menu`** (authenticated) — the agent-facing menu: workflow catalog,\nlocal/remote execution modes, and follow-up paths. The same data backs the\nMCP `get_menu` tool and `/llms.txt`."},"719":{"id":"/guides/api-33","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#discovery","content":"**`GET /api/version`** (unauthenticated) — product name, version, instance\nname."},"720":{"id":"/guides/api-34","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"Operations are organized into eight groups, exposed as OpenAPI tags:\n**workflows**, **runs**, **approvals**, **automation** (schedules + workflow\nendpoints), **library** (agents, skills, knowledge, hooks), **distribution**\n(bundles, packages), **admin** (tokens, secrets, audit, alerts, updates), and\n**system** (health, version, menu, dashboard, runners)."},"721":{"id":"/guides/api-35","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"Every grouped operation is also reachable at a stable `/api/v1` alias that\nmakes the group visible in the path — for example:"},"722":{"id":"/guides/api-36","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"Canonical"},"723":{"id":"/guides/api-37","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"Grouped alias"},"724":{"id":"/guides/api-38","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/workflows`"},"725":{"id":"/guides/api-39","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/v1/workflows`"},"726":{"id":"/guides/api-40","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/runs/:id`"},"727":{"id":"/guides/api-41","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/v1/runs/:id`"},"728":{"id":"/guides/api-42","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/run-drafts`"},"729":{"id":"/guides/api-43","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/v1/runs/drafts`"},"730":{"id":"/guides/api-44","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/schedules`"},"731":{"id":"/guides/api-45","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/v1/automation/schedules`"},"732":{"id":"/guides/api-46","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/agents`"},"733":{"id":"/guides/api-47","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/v1/library/agents`"},"734":{"id":"/guides/api-48","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/workflow-bundles`"},"735":{"id":"/guides/api-49","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/v1/distribution/bundles`"},"736":{"id":"/guides/api-50","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/tokens`"},"737":{"id":"/guides/api-51","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/v1/admin/tokens`"},"738":{"id":"/guides/api-52","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/menu`"},"739":{"id":"/guides/api-53","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/v1/system/menu`"},"740":{"id":"/guides/api-54","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"Aliases are the same registry entries registered twice, so they always share\nthe canonical route's handler, auth, and scopes; in `openapi.json` each alias\ncarries `x-canonical-path`. Unversioned `/api/...` paths remain fully\nsupported — use whichever reads better. The legacy `/api/capabilities/*`\npaths are deprecated aliases of `/api/workflows/*` and get no `/api/v1` form;\nnew clients should say *workflow* everywhere."},"741":{"id":"/guides/api-55","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#the-typical-flow","content":"List workflows, preflight your input, start the run, then poll it:"},"742":{"id":"/guides/api-56","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#the-typical-flow","content":"For agent-created runs, include a short human-readable `input.title` — it labels\nrun lists, approval cards, and handoffs. `executionMode` is `local` or `remote`;\n`run` also accepts an optional `responseEndpoint` (`{type: http|telegram,\nconfig}`) to have the terminal-state reply delivered when the run finishes\n(polling `/api/runs/:id` remains the canonical fallback), and an optional\n`budget` (`{maxTokens?, maxCostMicros?}`, also accepted as `input.budget`) that\nhard-caps the run's metered model usage — a breach terminates the run with the\ndistinct status `budget_exceeded`. Metered usage aggregates onto every run\nobject as `usage` and is detailed at `GET /api/runs/:id/usage`; see\nUsage metering & budgets."},"743":{"id":"/guides/api-57","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#the-typical-flow","content":"With `\"negotiate\": true`, a non-ready request returns the negotiation state\n(questions, blockers, warnings, plus a saved draft) instead of creating a run —\nfix the input and call again."},"744":{"id":"/guides/api-58","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Workflows and runs (`preflight` and `run` require `api` or `mcp` scope; reads\nrequire any token):"},"745":{"id":"/guides/api-59","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Method + path"},"746":{"id":"/guides/api-60","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Purpose"},"747":{"id":"/guides/api-61","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`GET /api/workflows`"},"748":{"id":"/guides/api-62","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"List workflows (`?q=` searches)"},"749":{"id":"/guides/api-63","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`GET /api/workflows/:id`"},"750":{"id":"/guides/api-64","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Describe a workflow and its input schema"},"751":{"id":"/guides/api-65","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`GET /api/workflows/:id/source`"},"752":{"id":"/guides/api-66","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Workflow source, parsed metadata, sections, graph"},"753":{"id":"/guides/api-67","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`POST /api/workflows/:id/preflight`"},"754":{"id":"/guides/api-68","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Dry-run preflight: `ready` / `needs_input` / `blocked`, nothing created"},"755":{"id":"/guides/api-69","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`POST /api/workflows/:id/run`"},"756":{"id":"/guides/api-70","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Run a workflow: `{input, executionMode, negotiate?}`"},"757":{"id":"/guides/api-71","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`POST /api/workflows` / `PATCH /api/workflows/:id`"},"758":{"id":"/guides/api-72","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Create/update a workflow (admin). Source is submitted as bytes or a `workflow.bundleId` — never a file path"},"759":{"id":"/guides/api-73","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`GET /api/runs`"},"760":{"id":"/guides/api-74","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"List runs (filter by `status`, `q`, `workflow`)"},"761":{"id":"/guides/api-75","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`GET /api/runs/:id`"},"762":{"id":"/guides/api-76","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Run status, outputs, error, response-delivery state"},"763":{"id":"/guides/api-77","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`GET /api/runs/:id/timeline`"},"764":{"id":"/guides/api-78","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Unified ascending timeline (`since=<iso>`, `limit=<n>`); backs `runyard tail`"},"765":{"id":"/guides/api-79","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`GET /api/runs/:id/usage`"},"766":{"id":"/guides/api-80","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Metered usage: aggregate totals, per-call records, budget, and `budgetStop`"},"767":{"id":"/guides/api-81","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`GET /api/runs/:id/events` · `/logs` · `/diagnostics`"},"768":{"id":"/guides/api-82","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Structured events, log lines, diagnostics + log summary"},"769":{"id":"/guides/api-83","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`GET /api/runs/:id/artifacts` · `GET /api/artifacts/:id/download`"},"770":{"id":"/guides/api-84","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"List a run's artifacts; download bytes"},"771":{"id":"/guides/api-85","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`POST /api/runs/:id/cancel` · `/rerun` · `/promote`"},"772":{"id":"/guides/api-86","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Cancel; re-queue with same/edited input; merge a successful isolated run into its target branch"},"773":{"id":"/guides/api-87","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`POST /api/runs/:id/pause` · `/resume`"},"774":{"id":"/guides/api-88","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Park an active run on a recoverable interruption (e.g. `credits_exhausted`; records pause metadata + the engine checkpoint, frees the runner slot); resume re-queues the same run and continues from the checkpoint when one exists"},"775":{"id":"/guides/api-89","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Other resources (see `/openapi.json` for the rest — schedules, catalog\nagents/skills/knowledge, hooks, workflow bundles and packages, workflow\nendpoints, runners, dashboard):"},"776":{"id":"/guides/api-90","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"t