peration"],[720,"Operations are organized into eight groups, exposed as OpenAPI tags:\n**workflows**, **runs**, **approvals**, **automation** (schedules + workflow\nendpoints), **library** (agents, skills, knowledge, hooks), **distribution**\n(bundles, packages), **admin** (tokens, secrets, audit, alerts, updates), and\n**system** (health, version, menu, dashboard, runners)."],[932,"Option"],[909,"Optional default chat/thread for non-approval notifications."],[1026,"Optional pre-seeded bootstrap admin/runner token (containers); on host installs one is generated into the data dir"],[957,"Options: `--units <units>` (systemd units to restart, default\n`runyard runyard-runner`) and `--grace-ms <ms>` (bounded drain window before\naborting — in-flight runs are never killed)."],[481,"Other consumers reference secrets **by name only**: hook profiles declare `secretNames`, and their readiness checks report missing *names*, never values."],[775,"Other resources (see `/openapi.json` for the rest — schedules, catalog\nagents/skills/knowledge, hooks, workflow bundles and packages, workflow\nendpoints, runners, dashboard):"],[223,"Outcome"],[1306,"Over MCP the same payload goes to `create_workflow` as the `workflow` argument. The response definition carries `workflow.bundleId` instead of the inline source — the bytes now live in the Hub DB. Runners fetch the bundle at execution time; nothing needs to exist on any runner's filesystem beforehand."],[774,"Park an active run on a recoverable interruption (e.g. `credits_exhausted`; records pause metadata + the engine checkpoint, frees the runner slot); resume re-queues the same run and continues from the checkpoint when one exists"],[369,"Parked on a recoverable external interruption (provider credits or quota exhausted, or an operator pause). Non-terminal: the run keeps its engine checkpoint, frees its runner slot, is never reaped, and waits for resume or cancel."],[291,"Path"],[349,"Paused runs (recoverable interruptions)"],[480,"Pa