ims the run — the Hub decrypts exactly those named secrets into an env map that rides the claim payload, and the runner injects them **only into the workflow's child process environment**. That is the sole path a plaintext value ever leaves the store:"],[521,"Preset"],[497,"Presets"],[1171,"Product name and version."],[1162,"Production posture"],[198,"Profiles are bounded on purpose"],[216,"Profiles reference secrets by **name only** (`secretNames`), declare typed `params` callers may fill, and can restrict which workflows may use them (`allowedCapabilities`)."],[432,"Provide `runAt` (an ISO timestamp) instead of `cron` to fire exactly once. A schedule takes one or the other."],[1000,"Provide secrets (`RUNYARD_HUB_SESSION_SECRET`, `SECRETS_ENC_KEY`,\n`RUNYARD_HUB_TOKEN`, agent API keys) via a `.env` file or your platform's secret\nmechanism. For production, pin images by `@sha256:` digest rather than mutable\ntags. Optional overlays (all off by default):"],[298,"Provider key stays on the Hub; the child only holds a run-scoped gateway token"],[1016,"Public URL of the Hub (e.g. `https://hub.example.com`); an `https` value enables production behavior"],[601,"Published source lives in the Hub database as **workflow bundles**: immutable, hash-addressed rows in the `workflow_bundles` table. Publishing is insert-only — every publish creates a new `(workflow slug, version)` row with a `sha256` of the source, so a bundle id permanently names the exact bytes that were published. Bundles are capped at 500 KB, listing never returns source bytes, and a workflow that references a missing bundle fails preflight rather than silently falling back to a file."],[1135,"Publishes the GitHub Release with generated notes — only after `test` and `sandbox-smoke` are green. A red run never publishes."],[585,"Purpose"],[746,"Purpose"],[777,"Purpose"],[794,"Purpose"],[809,"Purpose"],[899,"Purpose"],[1167,"Purpose"],[209,"Push a work branch to a configured remote. Protected branches (`main`, `m